this.add({id:377, 
title:"Create a Security Assessment Profile", 
body:" create security assessment profile to create security assessment profile: under profiles click + symbol. the  new custom profile  page opens. under  cloud provider , select cloud services provider click next .  under rules , select predefined custom rules applied profile. click next .  under attributes , specify profile attributes. under profile name , enter profile name. under profile description , enter short description profile. click save save profile. optionally, under  add to policy , click inside text box select policy list add profile policy. click  save apply changes . " });
this.add({id:378, 
title:"Create a Security Assessment Rule", 
body:" create security assessment rule to create security assessment rule: click new rule . the new custom rule page opens. under rule name , enter rule name. under cloud provider , select cloud services platform click save & continue . under severity , select rule severity drop-down list. the available options critical , high , medium , low . select level severity want assign rule. under definition , enter rule definition using domain specific language (dsl). for information dsl, see custom rules using domain specific language . alternatively, use import from rule option import modify existing rule. click save as draft continue working rule save save rule. click validate definition validate rule fix any syntax errors. click compliance tab specify compliance standards rule satisfy. standard : the compliance standard, like cis-awsfnd-1.2.0, nist-csf, etc. section : the section document describes compliance standard. control : the section control document describes compliance standard. for example, predefined rule cis-awsfnd-1.2.0-2-3 ensure s3 bucket cloudtrail logs publicly accessible defined cis aws foundations document. in example, cis-awsfnd-1.2.0 compliance standard, 2 section, 3 control. click +add specify new compliance standard rule satisfy. click save as draft continue working rule save save rule. click other tab specify rule description. click save as draft continue working rule save save rule. the rule displayed rules section profiles & page. click apply changes . " });
